transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi. My name is Raymond Neel. I ordered the ABC or whatever that is called.

Speaker 2: I ordered that over two weeks ago. Yeah, well over two weeks ago. I haven't received anything. I wanted to know what was going on.

Speaker 1: Okay, Raymond. I can help you out. Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 4-25-49.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. Okay, it looks like the pharmacy had it. It was too soon to fill, so they had it on hold until today.

Speaker 2: So let me message the pharmacy and tell them to ship it out.

Speaker 1: So the pharmacy hasn't shipped it yet?

Speaker 2: No, it was on hold. I think, I don't know why it was on hold.

Speaker 1: I can order it tomorrow.

Speaker 2: Can you figure it out?

Speaker 1: Yeah, order it.

Speaker 2: Okay, too soon to fill. Hold order until January 26th.

Speaker 1: So it's a controlled substance, so it's regulated by the state.

Speaker 2: And I guess you can't get so many within a certain quantity, you know, a certain amount of time.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh.

Speaker 2: So maybe if you're getting other ED medication from somewhere else, because you know the pharmacy has like, they have your whole record.

Speaker 1: Maybe they saw something else in there and that's why they put it on hold.

Speaker 2: But today's the 26th, so I'm going to message them to ship it out.

Speaker 1: Okay, please.

Speaker 2: Yeah, not a problem.

Speaker 1: How long will it take for them to get it to me?

Speaker 2: They'll ship it out to you tomorrow morning. It ships from Kentucky, so you should get it in about five days or less.

Speaker 1: Okay, I promise.

Speaker 2: That's what I was told when I ordered it, that I would have it in five days.

Speaker 1: When we place the order, we don't see the pharmacy notes until they update the profile.

Speaker 2: And it doesn't notify us unless, you know, you call in and it's like, where the hell is my order?

Speaker 1: Then it's like, oh, okay, yeah.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: See you tomorrow.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Can I get a confirmation to that?

Speaker 1: Sure.

Speaker 2: Do you have a pen?

Speaker 1: Yeah, hang on.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: It is 5B as in boy, 428375C as in cat, 2.

Speaker 2: Can you repeat that?

Speaker 1: It's 5B428375C, 2.

Speaker 2: Perfect.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: And I can track the order with that number?

Speaker 1: No, the pharmacy will email you a tracking number tomorrow.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Very good.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: I'm good now.

Speaker 1: All right, perfect.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
